President Biden has declared a major disaster for the Muscogee (Creek) Nation and authorized federal aid to assist with the recovery efforts from a severe winter storm that occurred from December 21 to December 25, 2022. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Roland W. Jackson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.